<main id="main-doc">

  <section class="main-section" id="Introduction">
    <header>Introduction</header>
    <p>JavaScript is a programming language.</p>
    <p>It is used to create interactive websites.</p>
    <code>console.log("Hello World");</code>
    <ul>
      <li>Client-side</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="main-section" id="Variables">
    <header>Variables</header>
    <p>Variables store data.</p>
    <p>You can use let, var, or const.</p>
    <code>let x = 10;</code>
    <ul>
      <li>let</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="main-section" id="Functions">
    <header>Functions</header>
    <p>Functions group code.</p>
    <p>They are reusable.</p>
    <code>function test() {}</code>
    <ul>
      <li>Reusable code</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="main-section" id="Loops">
    <header>Loops</header>
    <p>Loops repeat actions.</p>
    <p>for and while are common.</p>
    <code>for(let i=0;i<5;i++) {}</code>
    <ul>
      <li>for loop</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="main-section" id="Arrays">
    <header>Arrays</header>
    <p>Arrays store multiple values.</p>
    <p>They use index positions.</p>
    <code>const arr = [1,2,3];</code>
    <ul>
      <li>Index based</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
